FL,395,390,120,260,000,100
PN,39414
SC,0014
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F394A1779225068
OL,3,CReform UK and Andy Burnham to go head-
OL,4,Cto-head in by-election
OL,6,FSome 31% ranked Sir Keir as their
OL,7,Ffirst choice, followed by former
OL,8,Fdeputy prime minister Angela Rayner on
OL,9,F8%.
OL,11,FJust 4% ranked Wes Streeting as their
OL,12,Ffirst choice, with 57% saying he was
OL,13,Fwrong to resign as health secretary
OL,14,Fand 15% backing him in a head-to-head
OL,15,Fcontest with the Prime Minister.
OL,17,FIn a contest between Mr Burnham and
OL,18,FSir Keir, 59% said they would back the
OL,19,Fmayor while 37% would support the
OL,20,FPrime Minister.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}     G14/15
